      "text": "Key Concepts"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "**Percent** means \"per hundred.\" The symbol \\% \n represents $\\div 100$.",
        "**Converting percents to decimals:** Divide by 100 \n (move decimal point two places left).",
        "**Converting decimals to percents:** Multiply by 100 \n (move decimal point two places right).",
        "**Converting fractions to percents:** Divide \n numerator by denominator, then multiply by 100.",
        "**Converting percents to fractions:** Write percent \n over 100 and simplify.",
        "**The Percent Equation:** \n $\\text{Part} = \\text{Percent} \\times \\text{Whole}$",
        "**Percent Increase:** \n $\\frac{\\text{New} - \\text{Original}}{\\text{Original}} \\times 100\\%$",
        "**Percent Decrease:** \n $\\frac{\\text{Original} - \\text{New}}{\\text{Original}} \\times 100\\%$",
        "**Simple Interest:** $I = Prt$",
        "**Commission:** \n Commission Rate $\\times$ Total Sales"
      ]
    },
